# APA 7th Edition Reference Formatting

## In-Text Citations

### Basic Format
- **Author-Date Format:** Use (Author, Year) for in-text citations
- **Multiple Authors:** 
  - 2 authors: (Smith & Jones, 2023)
  - 3+ authors: (Smith et al., 2023)
- **Direct Quotes:** Include page numbers (Smith, 2023, p. 15) or (Smith, 2023, pp. 15-16)
- **No Author:** Use shortened title in quotes ("Article Title," 2023)

### Examples
```markdown
According to recent research (Smith, 2023), AI adoption is increasing.
Multiple studies have shown this trend (Johnson & Lee, 2022; Brown et al., 2023).
As stated: "AI will transform business operations" (Davis, 2023, p. 42).
```

## Reference List Format

### Journal Articles
**Format:** Author, A. A. (Year). Title of article. *Title of Journal*, Volume(Issue), pages. [DOI URL]

**Example:**
```markdown
Smith, J. A. (2023). Artificial intelligence in business transformation. *Journal of Business Technology*, 15(3), 45-67. https://doi.org/10.1234/jbt.2023.15.3.45
```

### Books
**Format:** Author, A. A. (Year). *Title of book*. Publisher. [DOI URL if available]

**Example:**
```markdown
Johnson, M. B. (2022). *Digital transformation strategies*. Academic Press. https://doi.org/10.1515/9781501519765
```

### Book Chapters
**Format:** Author, A. A. (Year). Title of chapter. In B. B. Editor (Ed.), *Title of book* (pp. xx-xx). Publisher. [DOI URL]

**Example:**
```markdown
Brown, L. C. (2023). AI implementation frameworks. In R. Davis (Ed.), *Modern business practices* (pp. 123-145). Business Publications. https://doi.org/10.1234/mbp.2023.ch7
```

### Conference Papers
**Format:** Author, A. A. (Year). Title of paper. In *Proceedings of Conference Name* (pp. xx-xx). Publisher. [DOI URL]

**Example:**
```markdown
Wilson, K. D. (2023). Machine learning in marketing. In *Proceedings of the International Conference on AI* (pp. 89-102). IEEE. https://doi.org/10.1109/icai.2023.456789
```

## DOI Requirements

### DOI Format
- **Always use full DOI URL:** https://doi.org/[DOI number]
- **Never use:** doi: prefix or dx.doi.org format
- **Make DOI clickable:** Ensure it's a proper hyperlink in markdown

### DOI Examples
```markdown
✅ Correct: https://doi.org/10.1234/journal.2023.001
❌ Incorrect: doi:10.1234/journal.2023.001
❌ Incorrect: http://dx.doi.org/10.1234/journal.2023.001
```

## Markdown Formatting Rules

### Text Formatting
- **Journal titles:** Use *italics* with asterisks
- **Book titles:** Use *italics* with asterisks
- **Article titles:** Regular text (no quotes in reference list)
- **Volume numbers:** Regular text
- **Issue numbers:** In parentheses after volume

### Special Cases
- **No DOI available:** Use URL if available, otherwise omit
- **Online-only sources:** Include retrieval date if content may change
- **Multiple DOIs:** Use the most official/publisher DOI

## Quality Checklist

Before finalizing references, ensure:
- [ ] All in-text citations have corresponding reference list entries
- [ ] All reference list entries follow exact APA 7 format
- [ ] All DOIs are properly formatted as clickable links
- [ ] Author names are correctly formatted (Last, F. M.)
- [ ] Journal titles are italicized
- [ ] Publication years are accurate
- [ ] Page numbers are included where applicable

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Mixing citation styles:** Don't mix APA with other formats
2. **Incorrect DOI format:** Always use https://doi.org/ prefix
3. **Missing italics:** Journal and book titles must be italicized
4. **Inconsistent punctuation:** Follow APA punctuation exactly
5. **Incomplete author names:** Use initials, not full first names
6. **Wrong date format:** Use (Year) not [Year] or Year.

